<page>
    <h1>
        Monocrystalline Silicon Boul
    </h1>
    <h3>
        Source
    </h3>
    <text><style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br/>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br/></style></text>
    <text>
        Monocrystalline silicon boule, made by smelting 32 <style color="0xbbffaa">silicon dusts</style> in an <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" hover-info="click link">Electric Blast Furnace</style> with a small pile of <style color="0xbbffaa">gallium arsenide dusts</style>, 
        requires a minimum coil temperature of <style color="0xff5555">1,784 K</style> to perform the process and can be smelted using the Cupronickel Coil. 
    </text>
    <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/silicon_boule"/>
    <br/>
    <text>
        One monocrystalline silicon boul can be cut into 16 <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:circuits/silicon_wafer" hover-info="click link">silicon wafers</style> in a <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/cutter" hover-info="click link">cutter</style>, which also requires a minimum MV voltage to process.
    </text>
    <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_silicon_boule_water"/>
    <br/>
</page>
       